{"bookId": "68f1ce4cc729e5251bd00430", "moduleId": "68f8d38b834dea3be41f0b19", "subjectId": "68f8d3db834dea3be41f0b55", "chapterId": "68f8d3ef834dea3be41f0b65", "subject": "Physics", "chapter": "Mechanical Properties of Solids", "count": 4, "questions": [{"id": 313071, "subject": "Physics", "chapter": "Mechanical Properties of Solids", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "Most Important Selected Qs for JEE Advanced", "q": "A horizontally oriented thin copper rod of length / is rotated about vertical axis passing thorugh its middle. The breaking stress of copper is $\\sigma$ and density is $\\rho$. The frequency of rotation at which this rod just ruptures is", "options": ["$\\sqrt{\\frac{\\sigma}{\\rho \\pi^2 l^2}} \\mathrm{rpm}$", "$\\sqrt{\\frac{\\sigma}{2 \\pi^2 \\rho l^2}} \\mathrm{rps}$", "$\\sqrt{\\frac{2 \\sigma}{\\pi^2 \\rho l^2}} \\mathrm{rps}$", "$\\sqrt{\\frac{3 \\sigma}{2 \\pi^2 \\rho l^2}} \\mathrm{rpm}$"], "answer": 2, "solution": "The correct answer is option (C)\n$\\begin{aligned} & T_{m a}=\\frac{m \\omega^2 \\ell}{8}=\\sigma \\times A \\\\ & \\frac{m \\omega^2 \\ell}{8}=\\sigma A \\\\ & \\omega=\\sqrt{\\frac{8 \\sigma}{\\rho \\ell^2}}=2 \\pi n \\\\ & n=\\sqrt{\\frac{2 \\sigma}{\\pi^2 \\rho \\ell^2}} r p s\\end{aligned}$", "difficulty": "Easy", "source": "Most Important Selected Qs for JEE Advanced", "_book": "68f1ce4cc729e5251bd00430", "_chapterKey": "68f1ce4cc729e5251bd00430__68f8d38b834dea3be41f0b19__68f8d3db834dea3be41f0b55__68f8d3ef834dea3be41f0b65"}, {"id": 313072, "subject": "Physics", "chapter": "Mechanical Properties of Solids", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "Most Important Selected Qs for JEE Advanced", "q": "A uniformly tapering conical wire is made from a material of Young&#39;s modulus <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Y</mi></math> and has a normal, unextended length <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math>. The radii, at the upper and lower ends of this conical wire, have values <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi></math>, respectively. The upper end of the wire is fixed to a rigid support and a mass <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi></math> is suspended from its lower end. The equilibrium extended length, of this wire, would equal:", "options": ["<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>9</mn></mrow></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>", "<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>9</mn></mrow></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>", "<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>", "<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi mathvaria